	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Feb 6th 6:12 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>ok guys, right now, we suck.&nbsp;&nbsp;we're terrible at melee and pretty much have crap as spells.  we're completely useless if there is a cleric and warrior in group... there are a few options to balance us out, and make the paladins a group worthy class.<br><br>ok, right now we suck a melee.  there are 2 solutions<br><br>1.  Give paladins some sort of critical hit.  we can't dual wield so give us something that  deals damage<br><br>2.  If not critical hit, give us dual wield.  that's another way we can deal more damage.  <br><br>     we shouldn't get both, cuz then we'd be warriors that can cast, so give us 1 or the other.<br><br>    if yer not gonna make the fighting better, giv us some better spells.<br><br>1. right now we have crap spells to cast in combat unless we are fighting undead, which unfortunately is not very often.  give paladins some sort of damage spell so that we can choose between using our mana for blasting or healing.<br><br>2. give us our spells earlier.  its absurd that a level 40 paladin has the same healing ability and worse buffs than a level 29 and down cleric.  bring down the spells atleast one cycle, or lower the gap between us getting spells.<br><br>       right now we are worse fighters than rangers and worse casters than sk's, and they get a friggin pet, come on!!.  sk's are useful in combat as are rangers and both are better casters... sure the concept of rangers bein the best fighters and paladins being the best defenders with the sk in the middle is a great concept, but its not happening...<br><br>if you work for verant, plz do something about this<br><br>hakadar gimlikin<br><br>33rd circle paladin of quellious<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
